---
@version: [2, current]
@description: Set a hook.
@lot:
  - string $id = null, callable $fn, float $stack = null, int $i = 1
  - array $id = [], callable $fn, float $stack = null, int $i = 1
@static: 1
@example: |
  // Named function
  function fn_route_enter() {
      echo '<mark>test</mark>';
  }
  Hook::set('route.enter', 'fn_route_enter', 1);

  // Un-named function
  Hook::set('route.enter', function() {
      echo '<mark>test</mark>';
  }, 1);

  // Multiple hook ID
  Hook::set(['route.enter', 'route.exit'], function() { â€¦ }, 1);
@example-note: `1` is the function execution priority. The smaller the value, the earlier the function will be executed. And functions with the same priority are executed in the order in which they were added to the hook. Default is `10`.
